tricks.description:
By locking onto an enemy or scan point and strafing left or right, then pressing R immediately after strafing, Samus' momentum can be maintainted. This is useful in crossing gaps.
Check the wiki for more details.
This trick covers breakable objects that one wouldn't expect to be broken with certain items.
Mainly used for bosses, requiring either fewer items or less health to beat a boss.
This trick allows Samus to jump farther than usual by holding L during the beginning of a jump.
Objects that normally need visors to be seen or accessed without the required visor, such as Power Conduits without Thermal Visor or Invisible Platforms without X-Ray Visor.
Some damage sources give Samus extra velocity, which can be used to give her a small boost.
A broad category for non-obvious movement which can't easily be classified using other tricks.
A technique where Samus can gain extra height by L-Jumping into certain slopes.
Samus can maneuver in unexpected ways by standing on small ledges, vines, railings, and other unlikely objects.
By using the vanilla Bomb Jump mechanic in unexpected places, Samus can clear jumps normally meant to require the use of other items.
Samus can stand on some non-obvious enemies and jump off of them for extra height.
When Samus starts behind some one-way barriers, repeatedly boosting with the boost ball can allow her to phase through them.

Bomb Jumping and unmorphing backwards to a wall or forwards from an overhang to get an instant unmorph, then jumping within 2/5 of a second after leaving the ground gives a height boost to reach higher ledges.
Check the wiki for more details.
Using Boost Ball, a well timed boost can be used to climb a wall
